{"name":"#Flame On","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"description":{"chat":"","gmnotes":"","short":"","value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You can wreathe yourself in flames that don’t harm you or your possessions, but turn away harm, increasing your natural armor bonus by +1. At 10th level and every four levels thereafter, this bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +4 at 18th level).</span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You also gain fire resistance equal to your elementalist level. Any creature striking you with its body or a handheld weapon deals normal damage but must make a Reflex save or @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.8LdyXZl9PeXXFE8O]{catch on fire} for 1d6 damage a round (creatures wielding melee weapons with reach are not subject to this damage if they attack you.) This increases to 1d8 at 7th level and 2d6 at 13th level. You can use this ability for 1 hour per day per planar guide level. This duration does not need to be consecutive, but it must be spent in 1 hour increments. Your planar guide is considered to always have this effect active and it does not count against your usage. At 7th level or higher, your guide becomes immune to fire.</span></p>","unidentified":""},"source":"","type":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"up to 1 hour/level/day","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"none","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"none","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":1,"per":""},"isActive":null,"ability":"","actionTarget":"","actionType":"other","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","rollNotes":"","damageNotes":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[{"name":"1-6 Flame On","formula":"1d6","types":{"acid":false,"cold":false,"electricity":false,"fire":true,"sonic":false,"bludgeoning":false,"piercing":false,"slashing":false,"healing":false},"group":null},{"name":"7-12 Flame On","formula":"1d8","types":{"aci